PostgresConf South Africa 2019, which forms part of the international PostgreSQL conference series, will take place from 8-9 October at The Wanderers Club in Johannesburg. The conference will include 19 presentations and three workshops featuring local and international speakers. The event will focus on new developments in PostgreSQL and cover the fundamentals for those new to Postgres or considering migrating from another database. This yearâ€™s talks include a wide range of topics covering performance tuning, auditing, vacuuming, control structures, and security. The three PostgreSQL workshops at the event are: For more information about the event, visit: PostgresConf South Africa 2019 website